[@Zucchini yellow mosaic virus#Virus*] ([$ZYMV#Virus*]) causes one of the most destructive diseases of [$cucurbits#Plant*] worldwide.
Although the virus has been present in China for more than 25years, there is little information about biological and molecular traits of [$ZYMV#Virus*] isolates from China.
This study aimed to characterize 26 [$ZYMV#Virus*] isolates from Xinjiang, China based on pathotypes, molecular variability and host range.
[$Phylogenetic analysis#Method*] of the complete sequences of the [$coat protein gene#Gene*] revealed three distinct groups (A, B and C), with four subgroups in A (I-IV).
All isolates from Xinjiang were placed in group C and subgroups A-I and A-II.
